name: Seagull at Pero's Bridge.
description: Pero's bridge was completed in 1999, it's a Bascule bridge, and its unique features are a part of its mechanism. The bridge is named for a man known as 'Pero' who was enslaved, he lived from 1753 to 1798, and had been moved to Bristol, England in 1783. | 2592x3888px | f/8.0, 1/800s, 50mm | Canon 400D and Lightroom | Photographed 2nd June 2021 on a walk around the harbour side with Julia.
